Author: Mikelius
Title: [ANN][ICO] MINDOL - Japanese Subculture Aimed for the Global Market
Body: MINDOL is a new world of currency in the global culture market.  Website | Telegram   What MINDOL Handles: Japanese Subculture Aimed for the Global Market  According to the Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry, the market scale of domestic contents industry including Japanese cinema, anime, TV programs, music, and games amounts to approximately 1,200 million yen.  However, this number represents only the domestic market, and the market size of the global is said to be several tens of times more. More than 230,000 participants from all over Europe register for Japan Expo held annually in France, and the event is held annually in different parts of the world. It is globally recognized cultural genre that even Steven Spielberg who visited Japan this year expressed as “I love Japanese pop culture, it’s fantastic!”  Based on such global current, the MINDOL project will create new contents in the subculture/pop culture genre such as anime, cinema, games, manga, and music, with “Cool Japan” as the central concept. In the contents industry, a single content is expressed in many different forms, and lead to a wide variety of businesses. Because of this, the respective markets succeed while influencing one another.  In this project, funds that will be the basis of content creation will be procured with MINDOL token, and users of the completed contents will be offered opportunities to pay with the MINDOL token in using these contents. By doing so, the new values generated in the respective markets will be unified and organized through MINDOL.  We hope to realize the continuous expansion of the MINDOL token market and assure the token’s stable asset value. We will hold the MINDOL token sales in order to realize these prospects.  Utilization of the Blockchain Technology  This project uses the blockchain technology that assures high transparency and credibility on the internet, mainly to realize the below 2 services.  1）Copyright Management  Permissions regarding different rights to do with projects and ideas developed by individuals, or pieces created by individuals will be managed on blockchain. By doing so, we will develop systems for giving permissions for use of copyrighted materials and for charging fees.  2）Transparency of Votes and Donations  We will build a highly transparent, anti-tamper platform that allows supporters to vote for/donate to talents or projects they like, and connect the beneficiaries with the supporters.   MINDOL Project Team Many Industry Professionals will Produce and Advance the MINDOL Project  LOCOMOTION, Inc., Representative, Terry Ito ● Famous programs: “Asakusa yangu yohinten,” “Minisuka police,” “Kyuyo meisai,” “Ariehen sekai,” etc.  TOUCH PLANNING GROUP Representative, Tatsuya Ariga ● Famous projects (mainly subculture): “Tama new town,” “Mote fuku,” “Ani-son café yumegaoka,” “Akiba na renchu,” “Cho-D,” etc.   Neal Schaffer, Global top consultant in social media strategy  A top class consultant who was named “Top 30 Social Salespeople in the World” and “Top 50 Social Media Power Influencers” by Forbes. In the web-zine Marketing’s 10 Biggest Thought Leaders published by Adobe, he was named as one of the top 10 world marketing leaders together with names such as the founder of Facebook, Mark Zuckerberg.  He will be handling promotion and branding of the MINDOL project contents in order to expand them not only in Japan, but in the world.   Gil Junger, Hollywood film director.  Gil Junger is a veteran producer/director who produced and directed 3 feature films, over 400 TV programs, and 7 TV movies, and won multiple awards.  His famous piece, “10 Things I Hate About You” not only was a huge commercial success, but discovered Heath Ledger and Julia Stiles who both later became Hollywood stars.  Heath Ledger won the Oscars for Best Supporting Actor for his role in “The Dark Knight”, and Julia Stiles has played important roles in the “Bourne” film series such as “Bourne Identity”.  The latest film, “Think Like a Dog” that has been shooting since May 1st features Megan Fox (“Transformers”, “Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles”) and Josh Duhamel (“Las Vegas”, “Transformers”), and has entered for the Toronto International Film Festival.
